Jul 13 2009	The Hotel Abri is wonderful!	Just returned home from a quick 3 night trip to San Francisco with my 18 year old daughter who will be attending college there in the fall. After much research, we decided to try the newly renovated Hotel Abri in the Union Square area. I've stayed at many hotels in the Union Square area in the past and I have to say this is my favorite and one of the best values! The staff at the front desk was very welcoming and friendly, the room was warm, inviting and very quiet, and the bed was so comfortable. Free WiFi. 2 large screen t.v.'s. Bathroom a little small but not bad - - loved that there were drawers and shelves for storage though. We stayed in an Urban Suite on the 5th floor on the courtyard side. The location is fabulous - - just a block from Bart, Muni, and the trolley, plus great shopping, restaurants and theatre within walking distance. My husband and I will be planning many future trips to visit our daughter when she's in school, and we will definitely plan to stay here again.	
