Jun 27 2009 	Hotel Abri: Super friendly home away from home!	With 91 rooms, Hotel Abri shines following its $10 million renovation. I came here for a conference and my coworker stayed across the street at Parc 55, also a very nice hotel but a lot more expensive. Hotel Abri provides cozy, albeit small rooms stylishly decorated in clean lines with a modern Asian flare. Rooms include huge flat screen tv, refrigerator, hairdryer, iron and ironing board, alarm clock/radio, air conditioning (which you seldom need in San Francisco). Room service is available. There is no exercise room but this is a city where you can do a ton of walking. My room faced into the courtyard so although we're in the heart of the city, it was quiet even with the windows open. Lots of great restaurants nearby and Hotel Abri provides a list of best breakfast and dinner spots. Larger suites are also available. The front desk staff was terrific -- very helpful when it came to navigating the city. I love this place. It's less expensive than bigger hotels and much quainter. Super place. Super experience.	
